    11	
    12	# Anti-Stuffing and Cardinality Caps
    13	
    14	<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
    15	
    16	## 1. OVERVIEW
    17	
    18	Stop a skill from gaming routing by spamming trigger phrases or crafting adversarial content designed to dominate the derived lane. Caps and density checks keep derived evidence honest.
    19	
    20	## 2. HOW IT WORKS
    21	
    22	`lib/derived/anti-stuffing.ts` enforces:
    23	
    24	1. A hard cap on the number of derived entries per skill.
    25	2. Repetition-density demotion when the same token appears with abnormally high frequency.
    26	3. Adversarial-fixture rejection using the fixture allowlist bundled in `scripts/fixtures/`.
    27	
    28	Demoted or rejected entries never reach the scorer, so stuffed fixtures cannot outrank honest candidates.
    29	
    30	## 3. SOURCE FILES
    31	
    32	### Implementation
    33	
